/td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Intelligence Corps</p></td><td><p>21</p></td><td><p>24</p></td><td><p>24</p></td><td><p>24</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>557</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>579</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>590</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>578</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>Requirements for professionally qualified officer intake into the regular trained strength</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Cap badge</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015-16 Requirement</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016-17 Requirement</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017-18 Requirement</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2018-19 Requirement</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Army Chaplains Department</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Army Medical Corps Professionally Qualified Officer</p></td><td><p>43</p></td><td><p>38</p></td><td><p>38</p></td><td><p>38</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Adjutant General’s Corps(Army Legal Services)</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Army Dental Corps</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Army Veterinary Corps</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Queen Alexandra’s Royal Army Nursing Corps</p></td><td><p>22</p></td><td><p>22</p></td><td><p>22</p></td><td><p>22</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>92</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>87</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>87</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>88</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><br /><p>In addition intake requirements for Regular to Regular Re-joiners are:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015-16 Requirement</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016-17 Requirement</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017-18</strong> <strong>Requirement</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2018-19 Requirement</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Regular to Regular Re-joiners</p></td><td><p>250</p></td><td><p>290</p></td><td><p>340</p></td><td><p>250</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>Outflow estimates are calculated twice a year. The outflow estimate for financial year 2015-16 is 8,920, 1,050 Officers and 7,870 Other Ranks (excluding Gurkhas). Outflow estimates are not endorsed beyond the current financial year, and are not broken down by skill or trade. Outflow is subject to a large number of internal and external factors and is reviewed regularly.</p><br /><p>Intake and outflow figures are single service estimates and have not been produced by Defence Statistics.</p><br /><br />","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","11382 ; 11454","2015-10-20T14:49:45.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420643/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420643/answer","20131219_Future_Reserves_2020.docx","20131219_Future_Reserves_2020.docx","20131219_Future_Reserves_2020","20131219_Future_Reserves_2020","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420643/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-10-12","Army","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the anticipated personnel (a) inflow and (b) outflow in each (i) rank and (ii) skill or trade in the regular Army over the next 10 years.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","11453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420644","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-10-20","<p>The Queen Victoria School is funded by the Army Top Level Budget. The annual net budget for financial year (FY) 2014-15 was £4.2 million. An additional £0.5 million income is also received from parental contributions and commercial use of the facilities. Running costs for FY 2014-15 which are funded by the Defence Infrastructure Organisation Top Level Budget were approximately £1.2 million including rates, utilities and maintenance</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-10-20T14:34:32.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420644/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420644/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420644/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-10-12","Queen Victoria School","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the annual budget is for running Queen Victoria School in Dunblane; and from what part of the Defence budget that funding is allocated.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","11415"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420645","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-10-20","<p>The total amount spent on Continuity of Education Allowance in independent schools in Scotland for financial year 2014-15 was £2,396,830 which has reduced from £3,647,810 for financial year 2008-09. 173 children were in receipt of Continuity of Education Allowance in Scottish schools for financial year 2014-15. The table below shows which five schools had the highest Continuity of Education Allowance spend in Scotland for that year.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>School</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Fettes College - Edinburgh</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Strathallan School - Forgandenny</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Lomond School - Helensburgh</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mary Erskine &amp; Syewart Melville College</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Gordonstoun School - Elgin</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>In line with Departmental Policy, all figures of five or more have been rounded to the nearest five.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-10-20T14:45:54.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420645/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420645/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420645/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-10-12","Armed Forces: Private Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department spent in Continuity of Education Allowance in independent schools in Scotland in financial year 2014-15; how many children were in receipt of Continuity of Education Allowance in Scottish schools in that year; and in which five schools had the highest Continuity of Education Allowance spend in Scotland in that year.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","11401"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420646","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-10-15","<p>As my hon. Friend, the Minister for Defence Procurement (Philip Dunne), stated in the House on 8 June 2015 (Official Report, column 892), the Ministry of Defence (MOD) has signed a land sale development partnership contract for the redevelopment of the Ashchurch site. We anticipate commencing the transfer of the site to our development partner, Vinci St Modwen, in phases beginning in 2018.</p><p>Transfer of the site is dependent on the MOD re-providing certain capabilities, which are currently located at Ashchurch, to other locations. This includes capabilities managed on behalf of the Department by Babcock following their acquisition of the Defence Support Group. Assessment studies are under way and recommendations are expected in summer 2016. We continue to regularly engage with Trades Union representatives to inform them of progress.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-10-15T15:04:24.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420646/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420646/answer","Hansard Extract 8 June 2015.docx","Hansard Extract 8 June 2015.docx","Defence Storage and Distribution Agency","Defence Storage and Distribution Agency","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420646/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-10-12","Defence Storage and Distribution Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his policy is on the future of the Defence Storage and Distribution Agency at Ashchurch near Tewkesbury; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","11418"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420647","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-10-20","<br /><p>HMS GRIMSBY (43 personnel), as part of the Standing NATO Mine Counter Measures Group 1 Task Group, took part in Ex Northern Coast off the coast of Denmark from 15-25 September 2015.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2015-10-20T14:43:18.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420647/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420647/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420647/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-10-12","NATO: Military Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) assets and (b) personnel of his Department took part in NATO Exercise Northern Coasts.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","11399"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420648","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-10-20","<br /><p>The steel for HMS Forth (as well as HMS Medway and HMS Trent) is sourced via Dent Steel Services (Yorkshire), who conduct shot blasting and priming, from SSAB of Stockholm (previously 'Swedish Steel') who are able to supply the grade of steel necessary for this application.</p><br />","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-10-20T14:33:46.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420648/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420648/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420648/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-10-12","HMS Forth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the origin was of the steel cut for the hull of HMS Forth.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","11400"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420649","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-10-15","<p>One Royal Fleet Auxiliary Landing Ship Dock (Auxiliary) - Cardigan Bay, with two Landing Craft Vehicle and Personnel (LCVP) and six Inflatable Raiding Craft, along with 104 Royal Marines took part in Exercise Pearl Dagger.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-10-15T15:03:55.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420649/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420649/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420649/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-10-12","Bahrain: Military Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) assets and (b) personnel of his Department took part in Exercise Pearl Dagger in conjunction with the Bahraini armed forces.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","11402"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420650","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-10-20","<p>The Ministry of Defence has no record of the report cited in paragraph three of the document reference D/VCDS&amp;2ndPUS/8/1/4 PR11 existing. It is assessed the relevant issue was dealt with before any report was written. There is therefore no copy available to be placed in the Library of the House.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-10-20T16:19:26.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420650/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420650/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420650/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-10-12","Tornado Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 10 June 2015 to Question 794, if he will place in the Library a copy of the report cited in paragraph 3 of document D/VCDS&2ndPUS/8/1/4 PR11.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","11461"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420651","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-10-20","<br /><br /><p>The information is not held in the format requested. However the table below shows, where available, the estimated number of people who have been members of the Reserve Forces in Northern Ireland as of 1 April in each of the last four years.</p><br /><br /><table><tbody><tr><td rowspan="2"><p><strong>SERVICE </strong></p></td><td colspan="4"><p><strong>YEAR </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Maritime Reserve</p></td><td><p>see note</p></td><td><p>100</p></td><td><p>100</p></td><td><p>100</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Army Reserve</p></td><td><p>1,740</p></td><td><p>1,680</p></td><td><p>1,650</p></td><td><p>1,760</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Air Force Reserve</p></td><td><p>see note</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>80</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Note – information not available.</p><p>- = zero or rounded to zero</p><br /><br /><p>The Future Reserves 20 Volunteer Reserve population includes mobilised Volunteer Reserves, High Readiness Reserves and those volunteer reserves serving on Full Time Reserve Service and Additional Duties Commitment.</p><br /><p>The figures are based on Service personnel’s stationed location and not their location of residence, where personnel work is not necessarily where they live.</p><br /><br />","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2015-10-20T14:36:47.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420651/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420651/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420651/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-10-12","Reserve Forces: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many people resident in Northern Ireland have been members of the reserve forces in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Sammy Wilson","East Antrim","Sammy Wilson","11478"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420652","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-10-20","<br /><br /><p>The information is not held in the format requested. However the table below shows, where available, the estimated number of people recruited into the Reserve Forces in Northern Ireland in the last three financial years.</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td rowspan="2"><p><strong>SERVICE </strong></p></td><td colspan="3"><p><strong>FINANCIAL YEAR </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013-14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014-15</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Maritime Reserve</p></td><td><p>see note</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Army Reserve</p></td><td><p>250</p></td><td><p>150</p></td><td><p>240</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Air Force Reserve</p></td><td><p>see note</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>60</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Note – information not available.</p><br /><p>The Future Reserves 20 Volunteer Reserve population includes mobilised Volunteer Reserves, High Readiness Reserves and those volunteer reserves serving on Full Time Reserve Service and Additional Duties Commitment.</p><br /><p>The figures are based on Service personnel’s stationed location and not their location of residence, where personnel work is not necessarily where they live.</p><br />","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2015-10-20T14:37:35.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420652/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420652/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420652/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-10-12","Reserve Forces: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many people resident in Northern Ireland have been recruited into the reserve forces in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Sammy Wilson","East Antrim","Sammy Wilson","11479"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420653","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-10-20","<br /><br /><p>The Reserves Experience events are aimed specifically at “home” civil servants representing the direct employees of HM Government, rather than the general public. The events are staged in support of the Civil Service 1% Challenge which was launched in 2014 with the aim of recruiting 1% of civil servants to the Reserve Forces by the end of financial year 2018-19. To this end, a small number of Reserves Experience events have been designed to build awareness and understanding of the Reserves, and ultimately to drive recruitment opportunities, amongst civil servants at all levels.</p><br /><p>Although a specific Reserves Experience event was not planned for Northern Ireland, Northern Ireland based “home” civil servants will already be aware of the Reserve opportunity through an extant programme of engagement, as well as more general recruiting activity conducted throughout Northern Ireland. Northern Ireland is already better recruited in terms of reservists per thousand population than the rest of the UK.</p><br />","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2015-10-20T14:38:20.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420653/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420653/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420653/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-10-12","Reserve Forces: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reason his Department has not proposed a reserve experience event for a location in Northern Ireland in 2015.","false","Biography information for Sammy Wilson","East Antrim","Sammy Wilson","11480"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420654","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-10-20","<p>The Army is delivering its recruiting operations in partnership with Capita through the Recruiting Partnering Project (RPP). In January 2014 a number of steps were taken by the Ministry of Defence to improve recruiting performance. These were set out by the former Defence Secretary, the right hon. Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Philip Hammond) in his statement on 14 January 2014 (Official Report, column 715). Since that statement, good progress has been made and a number of criteria for the achievement of Full Operating Capability have been met, but the go-live date for the ICT system has been delayed and is now scheduled for no later than April 2016.</p><br /><p>The financial benefits of the RPP are measured by comparing the cost of operating the service compared with the original financial baseline used by the project. Actual versus planned savings for the financial years (FY) 2012-13 to 2014-15 are as follows:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Savings (£ million)</p></td><td><p><br>2012-13</p></td><td><p><br>2013-14</p></td><td><p><br>2014-15</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Planned</p></td><td><p>-3.4</p></td><td><p>20.6</p></td><td><p>32.4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Actual</p></td><td><p>40.9</p></td><td><p>-4.9</p></td><td><p>-43.3</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><br /><p>Capita has been subject to the full contractual performance regime since the end of July 2015, and is now responsible for all interim costs until the new ICT solution is delivered. Forecast benefits across the life of the project have now reduced to around £220 million. The project costs remain within the original approval.</p><br /><p>The revised planned savings to be delivered under RPP between FY 2015-16 and 2021-22 are now as follows:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Savings (£ million)</p></td><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>2017-18</p></td><td><p>2018-19</p></td><td><p>2019-20</p></td><td><p>2020-21</p></td><td><p>2021-22</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Planned</p></td><td><p>-13.0</p></td><td><p>19.0</p></td><td><p>33.9</p></td><td><p>39.4</p></td><td><p>45.5</p></td><td><p>54.3</p></td><td><p>38.3</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>These figures correct those in the answer given by my hon. Friend the Minister for the Reserves (Julian Brazier) on 16 March 2015 to Question 225513, to the right hon. Member for Lagan Valley (Jeffrey M. Donaldson).</p><br />","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","11386 ; 11485","2015-10-20T15:22:36.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420654/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420654/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420654/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-10-12","Army: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the (a) planned and (b) actual savings to his Department were under the Army Recruiting Partnership Project in each financial year between 2012-13 and 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","11481"
