"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420730","Department of Health","false","2015-10-20","<p>The Deputy Director responsible for tobacco control holds quarterly meetings with representatives from Action on Smoking and Health (ASH) in order to monitor delivery according to the terms of the grant awarded under Section 64 of the Health and Social Care Act.</p><br /><p>There is no central record of every occasion on which the current or previous tobacco Deputy Directors and representatives of ASH were at the same meeting.</p><br /><p><strong></strong></p><p><strong></strong></p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","11300 ; 11416","2015-10-20T13:44:41.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420730/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420730/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420730/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","Action on Smoking and Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, on how many occasions officials of his Department have appeared alongside representatives of Action on Smoking and Health on public platforms in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","11301"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420731","Department of Health","false","2015-10-19","<p>The Department does not hold information related to translation services centrally. National Health Service organisations have a duty to follow equalities legislation. This includes making sure their communities can understand information about the NHS services and that patients and clinicians can communicate with each other.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-10-19T14:13:30.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420731/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420731/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420731/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","Primary Health Care: Translation Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the cost was of translation services in primary care provision in (a) England and (b) Wales in 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Mark Pritchard","The Wrekin","Mark Pritchard","11285"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420732","Cabinet Office","false","2015-10-15","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-10-15T13:51:04.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420732/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420732/answer","11327 FINAL.pdf","11327 FINAL.pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Melonama","UKSA Letter to Member - Melonama","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420732/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-12","Oesophageal Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many people have been diagnosed with oesophageal cancer in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","11327"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420733","Department of Health","false","2015-10-20","<p>Two influenza vaccines are in use; a needle-administered inactivated flu vaccine and a live attenuated vaccine administered as a nasal spray to children. Side effects of either influenza vaccine are generally mild and unlikely to require any form of pain relief such as paracetamol or aspirin.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-10-20T15:14:17.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420733/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420733/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420733/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","Influenza: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will provide for aspirin to be available on the NHS for people with ill health caused by an influenza vaccination.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","11335"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420734","Department of Health","false","2015-10-20","<p>The independent cancer taskforce published its report <em>Achieving World-Class Cancer Outcomes</em>: <em>A Strategy for England 2015-2020</em> in July 2015, which recognised early diagnosis as a key priority for improving cancer outcomes. Recommendation 21 in particular refers to Wave 2 of the Accelerate, Coordinate, Evaluate (ACE) programme, which specifically aims to speed up and improve diagnosis of cancers with non-specific but concerning symptoms through the use of a multidisciplinary diagnostic centre.</p><br /><p>NHS England is working with partners across the health system to consider how best to take the recommendations of the report forward.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-10-20T15:40:58.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420734/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420734/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420734/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","Pancreatic Cancer: Diagnosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to introduce earlier forms of diagnosis of pancreatic cancer on the NHS.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","11333"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420735","Department of Health","false","2015-10-20","<p>Improving the treatment and care of people with dementia, reducing the incidence of dementia and improving dementia research, is a key priority for the Government.</p><br /><p>My Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State has regular meetings with various stakeholders, including Royal Colleges, in which a wide range of topics are discussed. There have been no meetings to discuss the potential links between alcohol, tobacco and Alzheimer’s disease specifically.</p><p><strong></strong></p><p>Studies investigating whether alcohol consumption is linked to dementia risk have had mixed results and research is ongoing. However, very heavy drinking is known to cause alcohol-related dementia, also known as Wernicke-Korsakoff Syndrome.</p><br /><p>Public Health England (PHE) has made dementia risk reduction one of their seven public health priorities for the next five years. In May 2014 PHE and the UK Health Forum published the Blackfriars Consensus, a statement calling for action on dementia risk reduction which was signed by 60 organisations and individuals working on dementia and other non-communicable diseases, as well as by the Secretary of State and the Health Ministers from the devolved administrations.</p><br /><p>PHE is now working closely with the Alzheimer’s Society and a range of others partners to deliver concerted action to reduce people’s risk of dementia by supporting them to live healthier lives and manage pre-existing conditions that increase their risk of dementia. Their programme includes work to further develop the evidence base and improve modelling of incidence and prevalence, to embed dementia risk reduction messages into health improvement and secondary prevention activity, and to raise public and professional awareness and understanding of what can be done to reduce dementia risk.</p><br /><p>On the latter PHE is engaging with the Royal College of General Practitioners as well as others such as Health Education England and the relevant sector skills councils.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-10-20T14:39:07.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420735/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420735/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420735/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","Alzheimer's Disease: Alcoholic Drinks and Smoking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions he has had with the Royal Colleges on potential links between drinking alcohol and smoking tobacco and Alzheimer's disease.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","11325"
