known</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>6</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>8</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>6</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>7</p></td><td><p>11</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>TOTAL</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>52,418</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>66,195</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>69,826</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>77,559</p></td><td><p>75,672</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="13"><p><em>Source:</em> Hospital Episode Statistics (HES), Health and Social Care Information Centre</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>Note: </em></p><p>A finished admission episode is the first period of admitted patient care under one consultant within one healthcare provider.</p><br /><p>Admissions do not represent the number of patients, as a person may have more than one admission within the same period.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-10-20T15:54:01.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420736/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420736/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420736/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","Macular Degeneration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people in each Office for National Statistics age group were diagnosed with age-related macular degeneration in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","11334"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420737","Department of Health","false","2015-10-20","<p>Departmental officials also have regular discussions with supermarkets on a range of healthy eating issues including the sale of sugary drinks.Although some supermarkets and manufacturers have made significant announcements with regard to reducing the sugar in drinks, which Ministers have welcomed, the challenge to industry to make further progress remains.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-10-20T15:02:55.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420737/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420737/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420737/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","Drinks: Sugar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions he has had with supermarkets to reduce or stop the sale of sugary drinks.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","11326"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420738","Department of Health","false","2015-10-20","<p>31 local transformation plans, representing 54 clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) were submitted by the first wave deadline of 18 September. A total of 102 plans are expected to be submitted by 16 October representing the remaining 155 CCGs.</p><br /><p>CCGs were given two opportunities to submit plans – on the 18 September and 16 October 2015. The first submission date is in recognition that some CCGs were advanced in their plans for local improvement and already had a Children and Adult Mental Health strategy and plan in place. It is expected that the vast majority of submissions will have been received by 16 October 2015.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-10-20T14:23:08.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420738/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420738/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420738/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","Mental Health: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) submitted a local transformation plan for children and young people's mental health and wellbeing before the first-wave deadline of 18 September 2015; and how many CCGs have still to submit such a plan.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","11304"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420739","Department of Health","false","2015-10-15","<p>The information requested is not available. Spend on research funded directly by the Department’s National Institute for Health Research is categorised by Health Research Classification System (HRCS) health categories including ‘cancer’. There are no HRCS health sub-categories, such as for brain tumours or other cancer sites.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2015-10-15T09:19:21.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420739/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420739/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420739/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","Brain: Tumours","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much was spent by his Department on research into brain tumours in (a) 2012-13, (b) 2013-14 and (c) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Derek Thomas","St Ives","Derek Thomas","11318"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420740","Department of Health","false","2015-10-20","<p>There has never been a specific reference to psychological therapies in the NHS Constitution.</p><br /><p>For the most recent update, we did consult on whether to include a right to psychological therapies, as part of the wider right to drugs and treatments that have been recommended by the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE). However, the right to drugs and treatments reflects the legal funding requirement that applies to interventions recommended by NICE technology appraisal guidance. NICE has not been asked to undertake a technical appraisal of psychological therapies, so we decided that the most sensible outcome was to not include the phrase “psychological therapies” in the Constitution as it would otherwise risk confusion.</p><br /><p>There have been no specific discussions with NICE on parity of mental and physical health interventions. The majority of new drugs and significant license extensions, including for mental health conditions, are referred to NICE for the development of technology appraisal guidance. Ifin the future psychological therapies are recommended in NICE technology appraisal guidance and consequently mandated for use in the NHS, we will consider consulting once again on including a right to psychological therapies within the Constitution.</p><p><strong></strong></p><p><strong></strong></p><p><strong></strong></p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-10-20T13:42:24.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420740/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420740/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420740/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, on what basis his Department took the decision to remove from the NHS Constitution the phrase 'psychological therapies' from the drugs and treatments that have been recommended by NICE; and what discussions his Department has had with NICE on steps to address the lack of parity in the way interventions for mental and physical health are addressed.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","11305"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420741","Department of Health","false","2015-10-19","<p>Employers across the National Health Service are responsible for the mental health and wellbeing of their staff.</p><br /><p>The Department commissions NHS Employers to help trusts improve staff mental health and wellbeing through advice, guidance and good practice[1].</p><br /><p>In addition, trusts have access to local data from the NHS Staff Survey, the staff Friends and Family test as well as local information to help them develop and implement local improvement plans.</p><p>The recent launch of the <em>How are you feeling NHS?<strong>[2]</strong> </em>Toolkit by NHS Employers is aimed at enabling staff to talk more openly about their emotional health, improving the assessment of the impact emotional wellbeing has on staff and patients and enabling action planning to improve staff emotional health and wellbeing. Since it launched on 29 July it has had more than 16,000 views.</p><br /><p>[1] http://www.nhsemployers.org/search-results?q=supporting+staff+who+are+experiencing+mental+health+issues</p><p>[2] http://www.nhsemployers.org/your-workforce/retain-and-improve/staff-experience/health-work-and-wellbeing/protecting-staff-and-preventing-ill-health/how-are-you-feeling-nhs-toolkit</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-10-19T14:00:20.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420741/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420741/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420741/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","NHS: Occupational Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what provisions are in place to support and promote the mental wellbeing of the NHS workforce.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","11306"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420742","Department of Health","false","2015-10-16","<p>Copies of healthWRAP training materials have been placed in the Library.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-10-16T11:53:58.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420742/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420742/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420742/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","NHS: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will place in the Library a copy of all previous and current materials used for the healthWRAP training course.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","11322"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420743","Department of Health","false","2015-10-20","<p>Information on the number of people in contact with mental health services including those of whom who were in contact with consultant led services between 2011/12 and 2014/15 is given on the attached table <em>The number of people in contact with mental health services and, of those, the number who were in contact with consultant led services 2011/12 -2014/15. </em></p><br /><p>Mental health services are delivered by multidisciplinary teams with clinicians from various professional backgrounds working together in the delivery of care.</p><br /><p>Information on the proportion of people who received consultant-led mental health treatment within 18 weeks of referral is not held centrally.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-10-20T15:59:03.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420743/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420743/answer","Number of people in contact with mental health services 2011-15.xlsx","Number of people in contact with mental health services 2011-15.xlsx","People receiving mental health treatment 2011-15","People receiving mental health treatment 2011-15","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420743/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many adults received consultant-led mental health treatment in each of the last 10 years; what proportion of people receiving mental health support received consultant-led treatment in each such year; and what proportion of those people received that treatment within 18 weeks of referral in each such year.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","11307"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420744","Cabinet Office","false","2015-10-15","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-10-15T13:51:27.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420744/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420744/answer","11330 FINAL.pdf","11330 FINAL.pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Melonama","UKSA Letter to Member - Melonama","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420744/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-12","Skin Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many people in each Office for National Statistics age group were diagnosed with melanoma in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","11330"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420745","Department of Health","false","2015-10-20","<p>Information is not held in the format requested.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-10-20T14:55:52.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420745/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420745/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420745/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","Liver Diseases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people were diagnosed with primary biliary cirrhosis in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","11331"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420746","Department of Health","false","2015-10-20","<p>There is no National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) guidance on the use of the ioIAMD lens. Where NICE guidance does not exist on a particular treatment, it is for local National Health Service commissioners to make funding decisions based on an assessment of the available evidence and on the basis of an individual patient’s clinical circumstances.</p><br /><p>NHS commissioners are required to have in place clear and transparent arrangements for local decision-making on the funding of treatments and for considering exceptional funding requests.</p><br /><p>If a patient’s local clinical commissioning group, decides, on the basis of rational, proper consideration of the evidence, that a treatment should not be provided which the patient and their doctor have requested, patients must be provided with the reasons for that decision in writing.</p><br /><p>The Government has been clear that restricting access to services on the basis of cost alone is wrong and compromises patient care. Commissioning decisions should be made on the basis of the available evidence of clinical and cost effectiveness.</p><br /> <br />","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-10-20T16:05:26.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420746/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420746/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420746/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","Macular Degeneration: Medical Equipment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of when the iolAMD device for eye conditions will be available on the NHS.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","11336"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420747","Department of Health","false","2015-10-20","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence quality standard for diabetes sets out that people with diabetes should receive a structured educational programme as this is key to ensuring that they are able to manage their condition as successfully as possible.</p><br /><p>While there is still much room for improvement, the proportion of people with diabetes being offered structured education is rising. 16% of people newly diagnosed with diabetes were offered structured education in 2012/13 compared to just over 8% of those diagnosed in 2009. In the same period the number of people newly diagnosed with diabetes offered or attending structured education rose from 11% to over 18%.</p><br /><p>Improving the outcomes of people with and at risk of diabetes is of great concern to this Government and we will put forward our plans in due course.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-10-20T15:01:04.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420747/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420747/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420747/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","Diabetes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what support is available for people with diabetes to ensure that they can continue to live independently.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","11332"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420748","Department of Health","false","2015-10-20","<p>It is not possible to identify the number of people who have developed a cataract as a result of exposure to sunlight.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-10-20T16:03:50.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420748/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420748/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420748/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","Cataracts: Surgery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the number of people who have had cataract operations due to exposure to sunlight in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","11329"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420749","Department of Health","false","2015-10-20","<p>The NHS Standard Contract provides a mechanism through which providers of NHS-funded services, including acute services, can be held to account. The Contract includes detailed requirements in relation to the provision of safe, high-quality services and compliance with national policies and NHS Constitution standards. It includes mechanisms which commissioners can use to ensure that services to patients are of a high standard and that providers take prompt action to remedy any failings.</p><p>The Contract provides a national framework, but there is scope for commissioners to include local detail appropriate to the services being commissioned (service specifications, specific quality standards). Management of agreed contracts is undertaken not at a national level but by the local commissioner.</p><p>Commissioners, providers and representative bodies from all service sectors, as well as national stakeholder bodies including the Department of Health, have been invited to contribute to NHS England’s review of the NHS Standard Contract for 2016/17.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-10-20T13:32:16.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420749/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420749/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420749/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","Hospitals: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the operation of the NHS Standard Contract for acute services.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","11388"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420750","Department of Health","false","2015-10-20","<br /><p>The NHS Standard Contract is reviewed annually by NHS England. NHS England intends to publish an updated version of the Contract for consultation during the coming winter, with the final 2016/17 Contract being published in the New Year for use from 1 April 2016.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-10-20T13:30:55.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420750/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420750/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420750/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","Hospitals: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when he next plans to review the NHS Standard Contract for acute services.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","11389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420751","Department of Health","false","2015-10-19","<br /><p>Clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) are responsible for local decisions on services for patients, informed by a wide range of local clinicians. The shape of community nursing services is organised locally, following advice from clinicians. This commissioning process also takes into account the local authority’s views through the Joint Strategic Needs Assessment and the local Health and Wellbeing Strategy.</p><br /><p>NHS England is working with local CCGs to ensure that services are based on the need of the local population, within the resources available and on evidenced-based best practice.</p><br /><p>The latest available data from June 2015 shows that there are 5,033 district nurses in service. The following table contains the number of district nurses that were in service in each of the last five years.</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>2014</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>District Nurses in service</p></td><td><p>7,813</p></td><td><p>7,132</p></td><td><p>6,611</p></td><td><p>5,877</p></td><td><p>5,590</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em></em></p><p><em>Source: </em>Health and Social Care Information Centre, Provisional NHS Hospital and Community Health Service (HCHS) monthly workforce statistics</p><br /><p>The following table contains the number of district nurses in training in each of the last five completed financial years, with the exception of the 2013/14 data which was not collected centrally by Health Education England. Data is not yet available for the 2015/16 financial year.</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>2014/15</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>District Nurses in training</p></td><td><p>236</p></td><td><p>177</p></td><td><p>186</p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td><td><p>381</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em></em></p><p><em>Source: </em>multi professional education and training budget monitoring returns</p><br />","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-10-19T14:10:20.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420751/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420751/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420751/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-12","Community Nurses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many district nurses are (a) in training and (b) in service; and how many district nurses were (i) in training and (ii) in service in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","11390"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420752","Home Office","false","2015-10-22","<p>The most recent missing persons data report, covering the year 2012-2013, was published by the National Crime Agency in November 2014 and is available on the UK Missing Persons Bureau website. This report provides the number of children who were reported missing (in the age ranges 12 – 14 and 15 -17). The National Crime Agency intends to publish the annual reports covering 2013/14 and 2014/15 in spring 2016.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley","11391","2015-10-22T15:48:59.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420752/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420752/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420752/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-12","Missing Persons: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many children (a) under 16 and (b) under 18 were reported (i) missing and (ii) absent in each police force area for each year since 2012.","false","Biography information for Ann Coffey","Stockport","Ann Coffey","11392"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420753","Home Office","false","2015-10-22","<p>The most recent missing persons data report, covering the year 2012-2013, was published by the National Crime Agency in November 2014 and is available on the UK Missing Persons Bureau website. This report provides the number of children who were reported missing (in the age ranges 12 – 14 and 15 -17). The National Crime Agency intends to publish the annual reports covering 2013/14 and 2014/15 in spring 2016.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley","11392","2015-10-22T15:48:59.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420753/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420753/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420753/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-12","Missing Persons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when she expects the Missing Persons' Analysis Data for 2013-14 to be published.","false","Biography information for Ann Coffey","Stockport","Ann Coffey","11391"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420754","Home Office","false","2015-10-14","<p>The Home Office does not hold data centrally on the number of occasions when illegal and fake alcohol have been found by the police.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-10-14T16:41:20.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420754/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420754/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420754/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-12","Alcoholic Drinks: Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, on how many occasions (a) illegal and (b) fake alcohol have been found by police in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","11341"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420755","Home Office","false","2015-10-20","<p>The Home Office does not publish security co-operation agreements with international partners as to do so would undermine bilateral relations and prejudice our ability to conduct work under these agreements.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-10-20T16:08:40.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420755/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420755/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420755/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-12","Foreign Relations: Saudi Arabia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans her Department has to publish the Memorandum of Understanding with the government of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, signed in March 2014.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","11376"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420756","Home Office","false","2015-10-21","<p>There are currently 326,144 individuals who hold Security Industry Authority licences. Since 2010, 765,022 licences have been issued.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-10-21T15:41:15.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420756/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420756/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420756/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-12","Security Guards: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people in the UK are currently in possession of Security Industry Authority licences; and how many such licences were obtained since January 2010.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","11299"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420757","Home Office","false","2015-10-16","<p>The College of Policing delivers the fast track and direct entry programmes. According to its data, seven external officers and 25 internal officers started the fast track programme with the Metropolitan Police in September. There were 1,952 applicants for the 2015 external fast track programme, of which 421 were to the Metropolitan Police. The public need to have confidence that police officers have been subject to extensive vetting before they join, and it is for individual forces to make decisions on recruitment.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-10-16T09:22:46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420757/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420757/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420757/answer","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420757/answer/previousversion/23527","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-12","Metropolitan Police: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people were accepted onto the Metropolitan Police National Fast Track Programme in the last 12 months; and how many such people did not subsequently pass the vetting procedure and therefore did not take up their places on the programme.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","11309"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420758","Home Office","false","2015-10-22","<p>Recorded crime figures for the period 2010 to 2014 do not directly map on to the two categories in the question. Data on human trafficking for sexual exploitation is available for that period, and there were no cases of this crime type recorded by North Yorkshire police in the years requested.</p><p>A separate ‘modern slavery’ crime classification was introduced in April 2015 covering all forms of human trafficking, slavery, servitude and forced or compulsory labour. Figures for April to June 2015 are available in the statistical bulletin “Crime in England and Wales, year ending June 2015”, published by the Office for National Statistics on 15 October 2015.</p><p>The Crown Prosecution Service (CPS) flags cases related to human trafficking and forced labour in its Case Management System, regardless of whether the eventual prosecution is for human trafficking, slavery, servitude and forced and compulsory labour, or for another offence. The table below shows the number of defendants flagged for offences related to human trafficking and to slavery, servitude and forced or compulsory labour in the CPS North Yorkshire Area:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>2010-2011</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011-2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012-2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013-2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014-2015</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Prosecutions</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Convictions</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2015-10-22T15:51:15.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420758/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420758/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420758/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-12","Slavery: North Yorkshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many cases of (a) trafficking in human beings and (b) forced labour have been recorded by North Yorkshire Police for each year from 2010 to 2014; in how many such cases prosecutions were brought; and what the outcome was of those prosecutions.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","11291"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420759","Home Office","false","2015-10-15","<p>We take security extremely seriously in cases referred to us for resettlement, working closely with the UNHCR who have their own robust identification processes in place. When potential cases are submitted by the UNHCR for our consideration they are screened and considered by the Home Office for suitability for entry to the UK: we retain the right to reject individuals on security, war crimes or other grounds. For reasons of national security, we cannot provide further on the details of the screening process itself.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-10-15T16:35:02.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420759/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420759/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420759/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-12","Refugees: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what screening provisions the Government has put in place to prevent people who wish to cause the UK harm from entering the UK through the Syrian refugee resettlement programme.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","11295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420760","Home Office","false","2015-10-15","<p>The College of Policing sets standards of practice and is the professional body for those working in policing. In common with other organisations, the College does not routinely publish details of commercial contracts and has no plans to do so. In relation to international assistance, the College works closely with the Home Office, the Foreign and Commonwealth Office and other partners across government. It provides as much information as possible under the Freedom of Information Act, including the total income it has received from international activity.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-10-15T16:18:24.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420760/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420760/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420760/answer","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420760/answer/previousversion/23519","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-12","College of Policing: Saudi Arabia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans her Department has to publish the details of commercial arrangements with and training offered by the College of Policing to the government of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","11447"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420761","Home Office","false","2015-10-19","<p>The requested figures are shown in theattached table. The figures include all British passports issued by Her Majesty’s Passport Office and the Foreign and Commonwealth Office for the three categories requested.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-10-19T16:03:24.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420761/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420761/answer","11487 - Table.docx","11487 - Table.docx","Passports issued by HMPO & FCO","Passports issued by HMPO & FCO","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420761/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-12","Passports: British Nationals Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many passports have been issued to (a) British subjects, (b) British protected persons and (c) British overseas citizens in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","11487"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420762","Home Office","false","2015-10-15","<p>Home Office Ministers and officials have meetings with a wide variety of organisations and individuals. Details of these meetings are published on the Cabinet Office website on a quarterly basis.</p><p>I would be happy to consider further engagement as appropriate.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2015-10-15T16:07:44.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420762/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420762/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420762/answer","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420762/answer/previousversion/23525","Biography information for Karen Bradley","1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-12","Charities: Islam","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will meet representatives of the British Muslim charities sector to discuss concerns about the level of prejudice and unfair stigmatisation they may encounter in the course of their work; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Chris Leslie","Nottingham East","Chris Leslie","11422"
