"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420774","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-20","<p>The Terms of Reference for the Advisory Board on Female Offenders and its updated membership are set out below.</p><br /><p>Board members have considerable understanding of and expertise in addressing factors underlying women’s offending, including domestic abuse, and will take full account of these as the Board takes forward its programme of work.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","11375","2015-10-20T10:42:17.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420774/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420774/answer","ABFO Membership and Terms of Reference.doc","ABFO Membership and Terms of Reference.doc","ABFO Membership and Terms of Reference","ABFO Membership and Terms of Reference","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420774/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-12","Female Offenders Advisory Board","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 14 September 2015 to Question 8612, on female offenders, if he will publish the updated membership and terms of reference of the Advisory Board on Female Offenders.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","11374"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420775","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-20","<p>General guidance on making a will is available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/make-will" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/make-will</a> and advice, if required, can be sought from professional legal advisors. Responsibility for the law relating to wills in Northern Ireland is the responsibility of the Department of Justice in Northern Ireland and guidance is available at <a href="http://www.nidirect.gov.uk/making-a-will" target="_blank">http://www.nidirect.gov.uk/making-a-will</a>.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2015-10-20T11:11:19.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420775/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420775/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420775/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-12","Wills","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what guidance is provided to the public on preparing a will and testament.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","11340"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420776","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-20","<p>The Terms of Reference for the Advisory Board on Female Offenders and its updated membership are set out below.</p><br /><p>Board members have considerable understanding of and expertise in addressing factors underlying women’s offending, including domestic abuse, and will take full account of these as the Board takes forward its programme of work.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","11374","2015-10-20T10:42:17.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420776/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420776/answer","ABFO Membership and Terms of Reference.doc","ABFO Membership and Terms of Reference.doc","ABFO Membership and Terms of Reference","ABFO Membership and Terms of Reference","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420776/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-12","Female Offenders Advisory Board","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 14 September 2015 to Question 8612, on female offenders, what steps he is taking to ensure that addressing domestic abuse as a factor associated with offending by women remains a core part of the work of the Advisory Board on Female Offenders.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","11375"
