"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420778","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-20","<p>As at 30 June 2015 (latest date for which information is available), the number of offenders in prisons in England and Wales for cannabis related offences was 1,363.</p><br /><p>Information on Scotland and Northern Ireland are matters for the Scottish Government and Northern Ireland Executive respectively.</p><br /><p>These figures have been drawn from administrative IT systems which, as with any large scale recording system, are subject to possible errors with data entry and processing.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-10-20T16:30:01.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420778/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420778/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420778/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-12","Cannabis: Sentencing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people are currently detained in UK prisons for cannabis-related offences.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","11298"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420779","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-20","<p>This information is published online at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/tribunals-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/tribunals-statistics</a>.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-10-20T10:26:08.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420779/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420779/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420779/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-12","Employment Tribunals Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what change there has been in the number of employment tribunal claims since the introduction of employment tribunal fees in July 2013.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","11273"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420780","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-15","<p>Where a person steals somebody’s identity documents and/or uses somebody else’s identity to access a bank account or to make some other kind of financial gain, he or she can already be prosecuted under existing theft and fraud offences. We have no plans to create additional offences.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-10-15T14:09:10.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420780/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420780/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420780/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-12","Personation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether he plans to bring forward legislative proposals to make identity theft a criminal offence.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","11440"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420781","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-15","<p>The Information Commissioner’s Office has upheld the decision not to publish this Memorandum of Understanding. That correspondence can be found here: https://ico.org.uk/media/action-weve-taken/decision-notices/2015/1432375/fs_50579089.pdf.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-10-15T16:40:21.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420781/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420781/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420781/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-12","Foreign Relations: Saudi Arabia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what plans his Department has to publish the Memorandum of Understanding with the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, signed in September 2014.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","11446"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420782","Scotland Office","false","2015-10-20","<p>There have been a range of meetings on the issues around open cast restoration at Ministerial and Official level. This includes a number of meetings that both myself and colleagues have had with HM Treasury and the Department of Energy and Climate Change over a number of months.</p><br />","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-10-20T14:06:07.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420782/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420782/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420782/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-10-12","Carbon Emissions: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, pursuant to the Answer of 12 October 2015 to Question 10602, on which dates he has held meetings with HM Treasury on the potential effects of a carbon price support exemption scheme in Scotland in the last year.","false","Biography information for Alan Brown","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Alan Brown","11470"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420783","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-15","<p>In the five years 2011/12 to 2015/16, the Department has increased its spend on cycling in England from £1 per head to £3 per head. Local authorities also spend significant amounts on cycling and over the same period, total spend on cycling in England has increased from £2 per head to £6 per head. Spend is over £10 per head in the eight Cycle Ambition Cities and London.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>2011/12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013/14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014/15</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015/16</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DfT spend per head</p></td><td><p>£1</p></td><td><p>£2</p></td><td><p>£2</p></td><td><p>£2</p></td><td><p>£3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total spend per head</p></td><td><p>£2</p></td><td><p>£4</p></td><td><p>£5</p></td><td><p>£5</p></td><td><p>£6</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong></strong></p><p>In 2014-15, the Department’s dedicated cycling programmes were Bikeability, Cycle Ambition Cities, Cycling in National Parks and the Highways Agency’s cycling programme. The Department also funds cycling programmes through the Local Sustainable Transport Fund (LSTF), with 28% of the LSTF being spent on cycling.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-10-15T12:33:26.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420783/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420783/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420783/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-12","Cycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to his Department's press release, New plans to get more people cycling, published on 16 October 2014, what the statistical basis is of the statement that around £5 was spent per head on cycling.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","11472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420784","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-15","<p>Highways England is currently reviewing the list of sites most severely affected by noise from traffic using trunk roads and motorways in England. This is being conducted on a fair and transparent basis using criteria agreed with Highways England’s stakeholders. The section of the M60 adjacent to Thompson Close is one of 2,500 locations being reviewed. Highways England will write to the Hon. Member once the review is complete and a decision has been made about provision of a noise barrier at this location.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-10-15T12:40:28.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420784/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420784/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420784/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-12","Road Traffic: Denton and Reddish","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will take steps to bring forward work on a barrier at Thompson Close in Denton and Reddish constituency to protect residents against traffic noise.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","11491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420785","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-15","<p>The purpose of The Bowe Review - Senior Liaison Board is:</p><ul><li>to provide an opportunity for engagement during the Review with key senior stakeholders</li><li>to enable a two-way communication to update key stakeholders on progress with the Review and to receive their advice on carrying out the review</li></ul><p>The board has met three times during the course of the review:-</p><ul><li>24 March 2015</li><li>20 May 2015</li><li>24 June 2015</li></ul>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-10-15T12:22:49.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420785/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420785/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420785/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-12","Railways","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the purpose of his Department's Bowe Liaison Board is; and on what dates that board has met.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","11431"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420786","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-15","<p>Operators of bus services serving educational establishments are entitled to claim BSOG for these services as long as they are also available for members of the general public to catch. However, “closed” bus services – used only by students and staff of educational establishments, and from which the wider public are excluded - are not eligible for BSOG. When it came to our attention recently that some operators may have submitted claims for closed bus services the Department wrote to all operators claiming BSOG in England reminding them of which educational services are eligible for the grant. We will take strong measures where operators claim for such ineligible services in future. Accurate figures for how many operators or routes may have claimed for closed services during 2014/15 are not readily available.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-10-15T10:44:58.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420786/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420786/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420786/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-12","Bus Service Operators Grant: Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many claims were made by bus operators for Bus Service Operators Grant (BSOG) funding for school services that were not entitled to receive BSOG support in 2014-15; and how many operators made such claims.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","11430"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420787","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-19","<p>The Borders Railway is a matter for the Scottish Government in line with the Scottish Parliament’s legislative competence for the promotion and construction of railways that start, end and remain in Scotland. We look to the relevant local authorities and Local Enterprise Partnerships (LEPs) in the Transport for the North partnership, in developing a comprehensive transport strategy for the North of England, to decide whether to engage with the Scottish Government and other stakeholders on the commissioning of such assessments. The UK Government has established a £12bn Local Growth Fund (LGF) to support LEPs in delivering their priorities for supporting local economic growth.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-10-19T11:27:31.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420787/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420787/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420787/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-12","Railways: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department has taken to assess the (a) feasibility and (b) the potential economic and social effects on the North of England of extending the new Borders Railway to Carlisle.","false","Biography information for Calum Kerr","Berwickshire, Roxburgh and Selkirk","Calum Kerr","11458"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420788","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-20","<p>Decisions on access to the railway are a matter for the Office of Rail and Road (ORR). When considering applications for new or additional access to the network by a railway operator the ORR will consult interested parties, including other users of the network and funders, such as the Secretary of State, and take into account their views. In reaching a decision ORR must exercise its functions in a way that it considers best achieves its statutory duties.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-10-20T09:34:25.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420788/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420788/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420788/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-12","Railways: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will work with the Office of Rail and Road to ensure that the proposed new Edinburgh to Berwick train service via Reston and East Linton stations will not be impeded by pathways being allocated to long distance train operating companies.","false","Biography information for Calum Kerr","Berwickshire, Roxburgh and Selkirk","Calum Kerr","11459"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420789","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-20","<p>The Government is currently considering the large amount of very detailed analysis contained in the Airports Commission’s final report before taking any decisions on next steps.</p><br /><p>The Government will carefully consider all the evidence set out, including that on noise, air quality and costs, when making a decision on additional runway capacity.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","11394 ; 11397 ; 11398","2015-10-20T09:17:39.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420789/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420789/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420789/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-12","Heathrow Airport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the potentially constraining effect on Heathrow airport's growth of that airport's future carbon emissions.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","11393"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420790","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-20","<p>The Government has not undertaken any such an assessments.</p><br /><p>Proposals for airspace change in the UK are subject to the Civil Aviation Authority’s (CAA) Airspace Change Process. A key part of this process is the requirement for airspace change sponsors to consider the potential noise impacts of their proposal and to consult those who may be affected. The CAA takes full account of the potential noise impact when making its decision.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-10-20T09:30:18.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420790/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420790/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420790/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-12","Air Space: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate his Department has made of the number of people who will experience an increase in the effect of noise as a result of the current plan to modernise London's airspace; what assessment his Department has made of the geographical extent of that increase; and what effect the proposed Heathrow expansion would have on those estimates.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","11396"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420791","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-20","<p>The Government is currently considering the large amount of very detailed analysis contained in the Airports Commission’s final report before taking any decisions on next steps.</p><br /><p>The Government will carefully consider all the evidence set out, including that on noise, air quality and costs, when making a decision on additional runway capacity.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","11393 ; 11394 ; 11398","2015-10-20T09:17:41.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420791/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420791/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420791/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-12","Heathrow Airport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the potential (a) direct and (b) indirect costs to the public purse of the proposed expansion of Heathrow airport.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","11397"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420792","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-20","<p>The Government is currently considering the large amount of very detailed analysis contained in the Airports Commission’s final report before taking any decisions on next steps.</p><br /><p>The Government will carefully consider all the evidence set out, including that on noise, air quality and costs, when making a decision on additional runway capacity.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","11393 ; 11397 ; 11398","2015-10-20T09:17:40.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420792/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420792/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420792/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-12","Heathrow Airport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the safety and noise pollution implications of new flight paths likely to be required as a result of Heathrow expansion.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","11394"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420793","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-20","<p>Sir Howard Davies was required to complete and sign a register of interest disclosure form stating any potential conflict with his work in leading the independent Airports Commission. Registers of all the Commissioners’ interests are available on the Airports Commission’s website at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/airports-commissioners-conflicts-of-interest-disclosure" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/airports-commissioners-conflicts-of-interest-disclosure</a></p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-10-20T09:21:39.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420793/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420793/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420793/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-12","Airports Commission: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department took to ensure Sir Howard Davies was not subject to any conflicts of interest when he was appointed as Chair of the Airports Commission.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","11395"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420794","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-20","<p>Ministers in the Department for Transport are in regular contact with the Welsh Assembly on a variety of matters. However, Ministers have not received representations from the Welsh Government regarding HS2 and Barnett consequentials.</p><p>Details of ministerial meetings with external organisations are published quarterly and can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dft-ministerial-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings-january-to-march-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dft-ministerial-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings-january-to-march-2015</a></p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-10-20T09:10:55.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420794/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420794/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420794/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-12","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what representations he has received from the Welsh Government on the Barnett consequentials for Wales resulting from public expenditure on High Speed 2.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","11411"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420795","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-20","<p>The Government is currently considering the large amount of very detailed analysis contained in the Airports Commission’s final report before taking any decisions on next steps.</p><br /><p>The Government will carefully consider all the evidence set out, including that on noise, air quality and costs, when making a decision on additional runway capacity.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","11393 ; 11394 ; 11397","2015-10-20T09:17:41.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420795/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420795/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420795/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-12","Heathrow Airport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the implication for his policy of evidence in the Airports Commission consultation of November 2014 which shows that Heathrow expansion will result in no overall increase in the number of UK passengers, business passengers, flights or connectivity because it would be fed by re-distributing growth from other UK airports; and what assessment he has made of the potential effect of Heathrow expansion on the diversification of economic growth throughout the UK.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","11398"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420796","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-15","<p>The Government is currently considering the Airports Commission’s Final Report, including its recommendation for a new national independent aviation noise authority. Any decision to take forward such a body would be subject to consultation on its detailed functions.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-10-15T12:48:49.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420796/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420796/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420796/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-12","Aviation: Noise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make it his policy to create an independent aviation noise authority with a statutory right to be consulted on flight paths and other operating matters.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","11429"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420797","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-10-16","<p>The current processing times represent a stable position for both DWP and our Assessment Providers and reflect the significant progress made to improve the claims process by both parties over the preceding months. We continue to look at all of our processes and activities to identify any further areas for improvement, or to drive out even greater efficiency.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-10-16T13:00:25.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420797/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420797/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420797/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-12","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 8 September 2015 to Question 9645, for what reasons median end to end times for processing personal independence payments did not change between April 2015 and July 2015; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","11274"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420798","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-10-15","<p>Following the General Election the Work and Pensions Select Committee has a new membership and a new Chair. The treatment of any inquiries conducted by the Committee during the last Parliament is a matter for the new Committee to consider.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-10-15T16:11:10.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420798/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420798/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420798/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-12","Housing Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when the Government plans to respond to the fourth Report of the Work and Pensions Committee of Session 2013-14, Support for housing costs in the reformed welfare system, HC 479.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","11314"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420799","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-10-15","<p>The information as requested is not available.</p><p>DWP statisticians are looking to include information on Mandatory Reconsiderations in existing regular statistical publications. However, before DWP is able to do this, statisticians need to make sure that the data is accurate and fit for purpose and develop a robust methodology. When a decision has been made, we will pre-announce this in accordance with the UKSA release protocols</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-10-15T16:22:15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420799/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420799/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420799/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-12","Work Capability Assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people applied for mandatory reconsideration following a Work Capability Assessment (WCA) in the last 12 months; and for how many such people the WCA points score was changed.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","11311"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420800","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-10-15","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 2 July 2015 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-06-24/3938/" target="_blank">3938</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-10-15T12:39:44.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420800/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420800/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420800/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-12","Social Security Benefits: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when the Government plans to respond to the fifth Report of the Work and Pensions Committee of Session 2014-15, Benefit sanctions policy beyond the Oakley review, HC 814.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","11312"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420801","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-10-15","<p>The Government set out its assessment of the impacts of the policies in the Welfare Reform and Work Bill on 20th July. These are available on the Parliament website.</p><p><a href="http://services.parliament.uk/bills/2015-16/welfarereformandwork/documents.html" target="_blank">http://services.parliament.uk/bills/2015-16/welfarereformandwork/documents.html</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-10-15T12:30:02.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420801/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420801/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420801/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-12","Welfare Reform and Work Bill","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will publish equality impact assessments for the proposals in the Welfare Reform and Work Bill.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","11313"
