"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420803","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-10-15","<p>Government financial forecasts published in December 2014 outlined expectations that the transition phase for all new Universal Credit (UC) benefit claims will complete by June 2018.</p><p>The NAO Welfare Reform Report on UC outlined that the bulk of existing benefit claims will be migrated to UC by 2020 with the exception of some tax credit and employment service allowance claims which would be migrated thereafter.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-10-15T12:44:06.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420803/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420803/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420803/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-12","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when he expects (a) all new benefit claims to be treated as claims for universal credit and (b) all existing benefit claims to be transferred to universal credit.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","11320"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421162","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-15","<p>This Government will fully consult on our proposals, this session, before introducing legislation for a British Bill of Rights. Further details will be announced in due course.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2015-10-15T16:47:16.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421162/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421162/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421162/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-12","Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what progress the Government has  made on developing proposals for reform of the Human Rights Act 1998.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","901583"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421527","Attorney General","false","2015-10-15","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the answer I gave to the oral questions from the Hon. Member for Redditch and the Hon. Member for Lincoln earlier today.</p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2015-10-15T12:06:57.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421527/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421527/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421527/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2015-10-12","Crimes of Violence: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what recent steps the Crown Prosecution Service has taken to improve the conviction rate for violence against women and girls.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","901588"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421529","Attorney General","false","2015-10-15","<p>In the year to 31<sup>st </sup>December 2014, the Law Officers personally considered 469 cases and referred 128 offenders to the Court of Appeal under the unduly lenient sentence scheme. 86% of those offenders had their sentences increased, which included some of the most serious violent and sexual offences, including murder, rape and sexual assault. The full statistics for 2015 will be published early next year.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2015-10-15T11:54:07.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421529/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421529/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421529/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2015-10-12","Sentencing: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, how many times the Law Officers have referred a criminal sentence to the Court of Appeal for review because it was felt to be unduly lenient during the last twelve months.","false","Biography information for Huw Merriman","Bexhill and Battle","Huw Merriman","901591"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421530","Attorney General","false","2015-10-15","<p>While there is clearly some awareness of the legal framework applicable to social media, I nevertheless publish warnings online reminding people of their responsibilities, where appropriate. My office also on occasions sends tweets, warning social media users of the risks of being in contempt.</p><p><strong></strong>As far as the criminal law is concerned, the Crown Prosecution Service has issued detailed guidelines on prosecuting cases involving communications sent via social media.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2015-10-15T11:56:44.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421530/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421530/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421530/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2015-10-12","Social Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what steps he is taking to develop a greater level of public understanding of the legal framework for social media.","false","Biography information for Mark  Spencer","Sherwood","Mark Spencer","901586"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421540","Attorney General","false","2015-10-15","<p>The Crown Prosecution Service Counter Terrorism Division has a good record of successfully prosecuting terrorism cases, with a number of convictions relating to the conflict in Syria and Iraq. Many of those cases have received Law Officers consent to prosecute. They include individuals who have returned from training or fighting in Syria, those who have attempted to travel and those who have encouraged or supported others.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2015-10-15T12:35:43.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421540/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421540/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421540/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2015-10-12","Terrorism: Prosecutions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what recent assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the Crown Prosecution Service in prosecuting terrorism offences.","false","Biography information for Sir Henry Bellingham","North West Norfolk","Mr Henry Bellingham","901578"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419783","Attorney General","false","2015-10-15","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the answer I gave to the questions from the Hon. Member for Brighton Pavilion on the 12<sup>th</sup> of October 2015: (<a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-09-16/10466/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-09-16/10466/</a></p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2015-10-15T15:38:57.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419783/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419783/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419783/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2015-10-09","Syria: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what the full legal basis was for the RAF drone attack carried out in Syria on 21 August 2015; if he will arrange publication of the original legal guidance on which the decision to carry out the attack was made; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","10720"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419784","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-19","<p>Royal Mail, as the designated Universal Service Provider for the United Kingdom, is required under the Universal Service Obligation (USO) to deliver the universal service to all communities – urban and rural – throughout the UK – and that includes the communities of the constituency of Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross.</p><br /><p>However, some postcode areas around the country, which may include addresses in Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross, are subject to local exemptions under the USO. Such exemptions are only allowed where geographical conditions or other circumstances are considered to be exceptional by Ofcom, the independent regulator for postal services. These exceptions are carefully monitored by Ofcom and are subject to an established appeals process. Quality of service targets for all postcode areas are published quarterly by Royal Mail.</p><br /><p>Post Office Limited (POL) has no planned post office closures in the constituency. There is one possible planned change in Brora where there is a consultation underway to move the local post office to a new location in the community.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2015-10-19T16:30:17.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419784/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419784/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419784/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-09","Postal Services: Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what measures he has put in place to ensure that the Royal Mail Universal Service obligation remains active and in force across Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross constituency; and what information his Department holds on planned closures of post offices in that constituency.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","10711"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419785","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-19","<p>The Bristol and Bath Science Park provides a world-class environment for innovative businesses to locate and grow their operations. The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS) continues to work closely with the Homes and Communities Agency, the private sector development partners and local partners to ensure that the existing site is developed to its full potential.</p><p>The Homes and Communities Agency manages the development on behalf of BIS. The Department is the beneficial owner of the site and the Homes and Communities Agency holds the freehold rights.</p><p>A Local Steering Group has been established to steer the development, which includes representatives from the private sector development partners, the local universities (Bath, Bristol, and the University of the West of England), South Gloucestershire Council, West of England Local Enterprise Partnership, the National Composites Centre which is situated on the Science Park and is part of the High Value Manufacturing Catapult, Invest Bristol &amp; Bath, the Homes &amp; Communities Agency and BIS.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-10-19T13:10:03.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419785/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419785/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419785/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-09","Science: South West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what plans he has to expand the Bristol and Bath Science Park.","false","Biography information for Ben Howlett","Bath","Ben Howlett","10729"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419786","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-19","<p>Higher education institutions play an important role in their local areas. Several universities have undertaken individual studies of their impact on their local area, and such studies have generally found positive impacts. Universities UK and others have also assessed the important impact of universities on national growth.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-10-19T13:07:45.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419786/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419786/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419786/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-09","Universities: Economic Situation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent assessment he has made of the effect of universities on their local economy.","false","Biography information for Ben Howlett","Bath","Ben Howlett","10732"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419787","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-19","<p>The Arts and Humanities Research Council (AHRC) is sponsored by the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills and supports collaboration between Higher Education Institutions (HEIs) and the creative economy using a variety of mechanisms including knowledge exchange centres and collaborative doctoral studentships.</p><p>AHRC will invest £16m during the period 2012-16 in the Knowledge Exchange Hubs for the Creative Economy. These Hubs, based in Bristol, Dundee, London and Lancaster, have drawn over 350 businesses, 320 academics and 170 third sector organisations into new forms of collaboration.</p><p>Innovate UK encourages collaboration between HEIs and the creative economy through Knowledge Transfer Partnerships (8 currently being supported in the Creative Industries) and through support of the creative industries council’s strategy.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-10-19T13:05:55.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419787/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419787/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419787/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-09","Higher Education: Arts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps his Department is taking to encourage collaboration between higher education institutions and the creative economy.","false","Biography information for Ben Howlett","Bath","Ben Howlett","10733"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419788","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-19","<p>The Government publish on GOV.UK, on a country by country basis, details of sanctions regimes, arms embargoes and restrictions on the export of strategic goods currently implemented by the UK.</p><p>Arms embargoes ban the export of ‘arms and related material’. This covers military ammunition, weapons and goods. They may be imposed by a number of organisations, including the UN, the EU or the Organisation for Security and Cooperation in Europe. They may also be imposed at national level.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-10-19T14:57:00.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419788/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419788/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419788/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-09","Arms Trade: Export Controls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, to which countries UK weapons manufacturers are prohibited from selling arms.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","10746"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419789","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-10-15","This Government supports a responsible defence and security industry that helps meet the legitimate defence needs of other states, and contributes to their security and law and order. We take our arms export responsibilities very seriously and we operate one of the most rigorous and transparent arms export control regimes in the world. All defence and dual-use exports are required to meet the UK’s strict export control legislation and adhere to the UK international commitments including international treaties and obligations. Each application for an export licence is subject to rigorous case-by-case assessment against the Consolidated EU and National Arms Export Licensing Criteria. Risks around human rights violations are a key part of our assessment.","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-10-15T13:36:36.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419789/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419789/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419789/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-10-09","Arms Trade: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what his policy is on the sale of arms manufactured by UK companies to governments which have committed human rights abuses.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","10747"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419790","HM Treasury","false","2015-10-19","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) are unable to provide an individual breakdown of penalties and arrears. This would risk identifying individual employers outside of the naming policy and breach HMRC’s statutory duty of confidentiality.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-10-19T15:33:00.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419790/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419790/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419790/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-10-09","Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 10 September 2015 to Question 8778, what level of fine was levied on each company; and how much each such company owed in arrears.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","10776"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419791","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-14","<p>The Department works closely with HM Treasury on investment in science and research and is engaging at official and ministerial levels as part of the spending review.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-10-14T13:07:06.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419791/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419791/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419791/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-09","Science: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent discussions he has had with the Chancellor of the Exchequer on the science budget.","false","Biography information for Jeff Smith","Manchester, Withington","Jeff Smith","10681"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419792","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-19","<p>The Government acknowledges that some people are unhappy with the system of retentions as it stands, but it is an embedded feature of the construction industry. Therefore, our general approach is to work with the industry through the Construction Leadership Council and its supply chain payment charter; endorsing its commitment to zero retentions by 2025.</p><br /><p>That will involve quite far-reaching changes to the way the sector works. With regard to shorter-term measure to require retentions to be held in trust, we must act on the basis of evidence. That is why the Government is commissioning an analysis of the cost and benefit of retention payments to inform future action.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-10-19T13:04:32.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419792/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419792/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419792/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-09","Construction: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of a policy of requiring cash retentions from the construction industry to be placed in a trust in the event of insolvency.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","10702"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419793","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-28","<p>In determining the way forward on Advanced Learning Loans, the Department will take into account the forthcoming outcomes of the current Spending Review and draw upon the responses that were gathered through an extensive loans consultation last year.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-10-28T15:18:31.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419793/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419793/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419793/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-09","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what plans he has to extend the loan system available for over 24 year olds for Level 3 vocational and technical programmes to people aged between 19 and 24 year olds.","false","Biography information for James Cartlidge","South Suffolk","James Cartlidge","10791"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419794","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-15","<p>The Government takes its export responsibilities very seriously and aims to operate one of the most robust export control regimes in the world. Government policy is enshrined in the Consolidated EU and National Arms Export Licensing Criteria, known as the Consolidated Criteria. We rigorously examine every application on a case-by-case basis against the Consolidated Criteria and will only issue an export licence where to do so would be consistent with these criteria.</p><p>We undertake appropriate checks using both open and other sources when considering licence applications. To ensure a comprehensive and consistent approach, this will involve Desk and Post in the Foreign and Commonwealth Office and relevant experts from other Departments.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-10-15T15:42:23.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419794/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419794/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419794/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-09","Arms Trade: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what his policy is on the Government continuing to sign off arms export licenses for those countries identified as a cause for concern by the Committees on Arms Export Controls and the Foreign and Commonwealth Office; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","10798"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419795","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-15","<p>Information on the number of apprenticeship starts (first link) and achievements (second link) in the North East is published online at the FE Data Library:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/438150/apprenticeships-starts-by-geography-learner-demographics-and-sector-subject-area.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/438150/apprenticeships-starts-by-geography-learner-demographics-and-sector-subject-area.xls</a></p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/378238/apprenticeships-achievements-by-geography-learner-demographics-and-sector-subject-area.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/378238/apprenticeships-achievements-by-geography-learner-demographics-and-sector-subject-area.xls</a></p><p>We do not centrally collect information on the number of apprenticeship applicants from disadvantaged backgrounds who secure and complete an apprenticeship.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-10-15T15:44:49.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419795/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419795/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419795/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-09","Apprentices: North East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many apprenticeships are available in the North East; and how many applicants for such apprenticeships from disadvantaged backgrounds (a) secured and (b) completed apprenticeships in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","10851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419796","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-14","<p>I received advice from Departmental officials on the legality of supporting a steel company in difficulty. The state aid rules on giving rescue and restructuring aid to steel companies are clear and all such interventions are prohibited.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-10-14T16:16:24.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419796/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419796/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419796/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-09","Iron and Steel: Redcar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what advice the Government has received on Government intervention in the steelworks in Redcar and European Community state aid rules; and what discussions his Department has had on this issue.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","10876"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419797","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-22","<p>Details of Ministers' meetings with external organisations are published up to 31 March 2015 and can be accessed on Gov.uk at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=Ministers&amp;publication" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=Ministers&amp;publication</a>.</p><p>Further publications of Ministerial meetings will be published in due course across Government in the usual way.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-10-22T11:39:23.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419797/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419797/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419797/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-09","Trade Associations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with which trade associations he has met since his appointment.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","10918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419798","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-19","<p>The Government recognises the significant contribution made by charitable funders of research. The charity support element of Quality Related research funding, provided through the Higher Education Funding Council for England (HEFCE), has provided £198m per year over the period 2011-16 to support institutions leveraging funding from the charitable sector.</p><p>Decisions on any funding beyond 2015-16 will be subject to the outcome of the Spending Review later this year.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-10-19T13:11:30.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419798/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419798/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419798/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-09","Universities: Charities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will make it his policy to use the Charity Research Support Fund as a means to secure investment from the charitable sector into universities.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","10917"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419799","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-22","<p>Details of Ministers' meetings with external organisations are published up to 31 March 2015 and can be accessed on Gov.uk at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=Ministers&amp;publication" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=Ministers&amp;publication</a>.</p><p>Further publications of Ministerial meetings will be published in due course across Government in the usual way.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-10-22T11:40:27.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419799/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419799/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419799/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-09","Business","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many meetings he has held with businesses or industry associations in the (a) aerospace, (b) pharmaceutical, (c) automotive, (d) chemical and (e) financial services sectors since May 2015.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","10919"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419800","HM Treasury","false","2015-10-29","<p>The Parliament, and its then Treasury Select Committee, dissolved shortly after this report was published and HM Treasury was not able to prepare a response before dissolution.</p><br /><p>HM Treasury is considering the Committee’s recommendations and will be responding to the new Committee in due course.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","11212","2015-10-29T15:16:54.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419800/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419800/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419800/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-10-09","Small Businesses: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when his Department plans to respond to the Eleventh Report of the Treasury Committee, Conduct and competition in SME lending, Session 2014-15, HC 204, published on 10 March 2015.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","10920"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419801","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-19","<p>The Government’s Productivity plan – “Fixing the foundations: Creating a more prosperous nation” - reiterated our commitment to excellence in science and research, facilitated through a dual support system.</p><p>In 2013 the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills published a review of the dual funding system and research income across universities, including analysis of the ways in which UK academics can maximise their impact (available on Gov.uk).</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-10-19T14:04:56.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419801/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419801/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419801/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-09","Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment his Department has made of the effectiveness of the existing system for dual support for research in providing stability for research infrastructure and supporting competition of research grants; and what plans he has to review that system's use.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","10924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419802","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-14","<p>We have made no such assessment. However, the UK was the first country to publish a National Action Plan to implement the UN Guiding Principles on Business and Human Rights which sets out the Government’s expectation of business behaviour wherever they operate, including complying with all applicable laws and honouring the principles of internationally recognised human rights when faced with conflicting requirements.</p><p>Company directors of UK-based businesses also have a duty to act to promote the success of the company, and in doing so have regard for a number of factors including the interests of the company's employees. To demonstrate this consideration, companies are required to report information on employee matters, where necessary for an understanding of their business.</p><p>Furthermore, the Home Office will shortly be introducing regulations that will require businesses with a turnover of £36million to report on the measures they are taking to ensure that modern slavery and human trafficking are not present in their supply chains.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-10-14T14:53:10.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419802/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419802/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419802/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-09","Overseas Companies: Conditions of Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent assessment he has made of the employment conduct abroad of companies which are based in the UK; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","10928"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419803","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-23","<p>Progress on the UK’s National Action Plan to implement the UN Guiding Principles on Business and Human Rights is covered in the Foreign and Commonwealth Office’s Human Rights and Democracy annual report, last published in March 2015. We have made considerable progress, for example on improved reporting requirements. We will continue to update our action plan, reflecting the progress we have made as well as covering other related action taking place across Government such as the Modern Slavery Act.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-10-23T13:39:44.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419803/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419803/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419803/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-09","Business: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent assessment he has made of the progress achieved by the UK Business and Human Rights Action Plan against the aims and objectives set out in it.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","10929"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419804","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-19","<p>Bilateral trade in goods and services between the UK and Israel was £4.6 billion in 2013 (Source: Pink Book 2014). Figures for 2014 covering trade in both goods and services will be published by the Office for National Statistics on 30 October in the 2015 edition of the Pink Book.</p><br /><p>UK Trade and Investment engage in promotion activities which focus on promoting the UK’s financial services, healthcare and food and drink sectors to the Israeli business community.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-10-19T15:53:35.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419804/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419804/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419804/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-09","Overseas Trade: Israel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the level of trade was between Israel and the UK in 2013-14; and what steps he is taking to increase bilateral trade with Israel.","false","Biography information for Mark Pritchard","The Wrekin","Mark Pritchard","10977"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419805","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-19","<p>European Space Agency has no active nuclear engine programme and we are not aware of any activities taking place with regards to such technology in the UK.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-10-19T13:08:59.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419805/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419805/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419805/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-09","Spacecraft: Nuclear Engineering","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what collaboration is taking place between universities, space companies and the European Space Agency on developing nuclear engine technology for future spacecraft.","false","Biography information for Mark Pritchard","The Wrekin","Mark Pritchard","10980"
